        <seg th:sID="C28_app181-fMS"/>
        world,
        <seg th:eID="C28_app181-fMS"/>
    &amp; my manners were calmer <lb xmlns="" n="c57-0134__main__18"/>&amp; more composed than they had ever been <lb xmlns="" n="c57-0134__main__19"/>since 
        <seg th:sID="C28_app183-fMS"/>
        my
        <seg th:eID="C28_app183-fMS"/>
    journey to 
        <seg th:sID="C28_app185-fMS"/>
        the Sea of Ice. Even <lb xmlns="" n="c57-0134__main__20"/>my father who watched me as the bird <lb xmlns="" n="c57-0134__main__21"/>does its <del xmlns="" rend="strikethrough" xml:id="c57-0134__main__d4e24922">n</del> nestling was deceived and thought <lb xmlns="" n="c57-0134__main__22"/>that the black melancholy which had <lb xmlns="" n="c57-0134__main__23"/>oppressed me was quitting me for ever <lb xmlns="" n="c57-0134__main__24"/>and that my native country &amp; the society <lb xmlns="" n="c57-0134__main__25"/>of my friends would entirely restore me to <lb xmlns="" n="c57-0134__main__26"/>my former health &amp; vivacity.
